rComments: TLDR: Don't take this class unless you NEED it for a credit... Despite the professor's fascination with the topic, lectures were comprised of "group discussions". Harshly put, having a robot recite the text would've been more informative. After final exam, she even changed the total marks because one question was on something not on the syllabus.

I will rather eat my own limbs than going to her class and I felt like she does not know the class materials as well. she is confuses in class just like us so just read the textbook materials and dont bother going to the lectures.

Gets defensive when you ask questions, taking it personally that you don't understand and will not answer questions she does not like. She clearly likes Training and Development, but did not like the students or the environment. Her MC are also incredibly difficult but short answers are a joke. Read the textbook -dont bother with lecture
A very nice human being who cares for her students. Her classes are great too.
A very nice professor who teaches well and is lenient with marks. The class avg was B+
She's much better teaching MGT363 than MGT460. The very last questions for her exams are very hit or miss. Other than that, if you work real hard in this class, you can get a decent grade. B+ or A-
